2022. I can’t thank God enough for this year. The absolute best year of my life and I can’t be thankful enough to all the people who have poured so much love into my family’s lives! Thank you so much for this year and I can’t wait to see what’s in store for this next year! Cheers to 2023!

Words can’t describe the sadness that all of us are feeling right now. But I don’t want to mention that. I want to talk about and celebrate the life that my brother Anton Walkes lived… Every time I walked into a room with him immediately I’m smiling and laughing and we are telling stories or making fun of each other or someone in the locker room. He brought so much joy and laughter to everyone around him. We have had so many fun times together over the years and so many good memories. All of his friends, teammates, and family know about his energy and how you just wanted to be around him all the time. And what an amazing dad to Ayla. A great example to all of us fathers and I learned from you and am still learning from you. A great footballer and fighter and teammate on the field and it was amazing to share a locker room with you for so many years… I’m sad now but looking at videos of us is still now bringing me smiles and laughter because that’s just what you do brother. You will be truly missed. But I know you are in paradise now and that makes me happy because I know you are up there smiling. I love you brother. Rest easy ❤️

6 months has flown by. I’m so happy and proud to be your dad. It’s crazy how quickly you’ve grown up. This little dude is already crawling and sitting up and talking up a storm. I’m so excited to see what the next 6 months has in store! I love you my lil Noah pups. #6monthsold #prouddad #cookiemonster

It’s taken me awhile to make this post. Saying bye to something you have given your entire life to. Something that you have dedicated everything you have to since you were 3 years old. A poor kid from El Paso that never should have made it.
Soccer I just want to say thank you. Thank you for all of the memories. For the countless friends I’ve made all over the world. For providing me and my family with incredible moments that I will never forget. I will always cherish game days where the butterflies and excitement and nervousness are almost overwhelming until you touch that ball that you know better than your own hands. Playing in front of family and friends and fans and that pressure to perform then succeeding and getting a win. Training days with the boys of digging in and working to your physical limit together while trying to achieve respect and victory. The locker room of banter and joy and forming relationships that will last a life time.
I’m sad but I am ready and I’m excited. I’m ready to take on this next chapter of my life. I’m ready to take that passion and drive that I had for soccer and turn it to my new passion and my new goals. I’m excited for this next step but I needed to say thank you. First and foremost thank you God for making all of this happen. Without you I can do nothing, with you I can do everything. And I really did everything. More then I could ever have imagined. Thank you to my family for all the sacrifice that you had to make and the unwavering support you all have had for me my entire life. Thank you to all the coaches who have taken a chance on me and taught me to earn what I get everyday on the pitch. Thank you to my friends and teammates for all the experiences and having my back through the journey. Thank you to all the support staff at the different clubs who don’t always get all the recognition you deserve but without you all nothing would ever be possible. Thank you to the fans for all the love and support over the years and that atmosphere you guys create which makes it so special. Thank you. Thank you soccer.

What an awesome family joint birthday party 🥳 Happy Birthday to my beautiful sweet niece Kapri! I’m so happy you had a great day, but stop getting so big please. And Happy Birthday big bro! Thank you for everything this year. I’m so grateful for you. Noah definitely won best dressed by the way 😂

What an incredible and unexpected weekend! Big thank you to @zala_f3 for the amazing experience. And a huge shoutout to @tst7v7 had a blast! See you all next year!

Happy Father’s Day to my pops and to all the dads out there. First one for me and wow it was special. This little man changed my life and I am so grateful to be your dad. I will always be there for you son. God has blessed me so much my whole life but the gift of being a father is something I will thank Him for everyday. A dads love is something words can’t explain. I love you Noah pups and what a day we had!

Very happy to announce that I am now officially a fully licensed wealth manager. The last 6 months have been a grind. From retiring from professional soccer to having to get back in the books and pass all these tests, it was not easy to say the least but it’s crazy what you can do when you put your mind to something. I took my drive and passion I had on the field and focused on these new goals and thank God I’ve now achieved them. Beyond excited for my new career and can’t wait to help people plan a better future for themselves and their families! #phil413 🙏🏼 #joga

Happy 1st Birthday buddy! What a great start to your birthday week. You are truly the joy of my life and I keep loving you more and more as you grow and keep getting bigger and bigger. This year had so many huge moments and I am so grateful for these special times. I love being your dad and can’t wait to see the next big moment. I love you son. Happy Birthday Noah pups!

Thank you to @upper90gol and @jvallejo83 for having me on this trip down to Honduras. It was honestly eye opening and really gives you a new perspective. The joy and happiness these kids have in the circumstances they are in is incredible. And the work that my good friend @marlonpena2 is doing down there in these communities is life changing for these kids. God is doing amazing things in these communities and I am honored to have been a part of it. Can’t wait to go back next year. Mi familia nueva en San Pedro, Honduras ❤️
